The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Chinsurah, March 31: Three schoolboys returning home on a motorbike after a football match were killed last evening when lightning struck them during a Norwester.    
	Class IX students Jhantu Roy and Jayanta Roy and Class VIII boy Santu Mondal were killed at Akna village in Hooghly, 60km from Calcutta.         
	Shimla: A Bengal tiger dragged a fisherman into the Sunderbans on Tuesday. A forest official said that at Lahiripur in South 24-Parganas Gosaba, 150km from Calcu-tta, the animal did not give any chance to the others looking for fish and crabs nearby to res-cue their mate. Gunasindhu Mondals body has not been found yet.         
	Chinsurah: A police officer inspecting a crash site on Durgapur Expressway was crushed by a truck on Tuesday. Ranjit Dutta, 48, an ass- istant sub-inspector of Gurap police station, had gone there with a brake van to clear the highway, where a Calcutta-bound oil tanker had collided with a container truck. The cleaner of the brake van, Shibsambhu Roy, 28, was also killed.                                                                                                                                                                       
